{{Quote|Chandrila has always encouraged and fostered free, responsible speech, and it would appear that these workers took every measure to ensure their absence would not endanger anyone.|Tanis Mothma|<ref name="HNN" />}}
'''Tanis Mothma''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Politics|politician]] who served as [[Governor/Legends|governor]] of [[Hanna City/Legends|Hanna City]] on [[Chandrila/Legends|Chandrila]] during the [[Standard year/Legends|years]] prior to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. [[Mon Mothma's father/Legends|Her husband]] was an [[Arbiter-general/Legends|arbiter-general]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and their daughter, [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] became the [[Senator/Legends|senator]] of the [[Bormea sector/Legends|Bormea sector]].

==Biography==
Tanis Mothma was a [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="Species" /> [[Gender/Legends|female]] who resided on [[Chandrila/Legends|Chandrila]]. She was [[Marriage/Legends|married]] to a [[Mon Mothma's father/Legends|man]] who served as an [[Arbiter-general/Legends|arbiter-general]] for the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], and the pair had a daughter, [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]]. Mothma served as [[Governor/Legends|governor]]<ref name="SWS" /> of [[Hanna City/Legends|Hanna City]] in the lead up to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="HNN" /> She taught her daughter how to administer, organize, and lead.<ref name="SWS" /> In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], Mothma commented on the walk-out by the planet's [[Public Safety Commission]]&mdash;protesting over the vote to create a [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]]&mdash;noting that they had done everything possible to ensure that their strike had not endangered others by programming [[Droid/Legends|droids]] to cover the increased workload.<ref name="HNN" /> Eventually, Mothma was replaced as governor of Hanna City by [[Jovive Centi]].<ref name="CCW" />

